{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNMapSnapshotter","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSObject","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSObject"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can change the snapshotter’s options at any time and reuse the snapshotter","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for multiple distinct snapshots; however, the snapshotter can only generate one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshot at a time. If you need to generate multiple snapshots concurrently,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create multiple snapshotter objects.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an interactive map, use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class. Both "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" are compatible with offline packs managed by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOfflineStorage","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"From a snapshot, you can obtain an image and convert geographic coordinates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the image’s coordinate space in order to superimpose markers and overlays. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you do not need offline map functionality, you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" class in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/mapbox\/MapboxStatic.swift\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to generate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"static map images with overlays."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Example","text":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let camera = MLNMapCamera(lookingAtCenter: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.7184, longitude:","-122.4365), altitude: 100, pitch: 20, heading: 0)","","let options = MLNMapSnapshotOptions(styleURL: MLNStyle.satelliteStreetsStyleURL, camera: camera,","size: CGSize(width: 320, height: 480)) options.zoomLevel = 10","","let snapshotter = MLNMapSnapshotter(options: options)","snapshotter.start { (snapshot, error) in","    if let error = error {","        fatalError(error.localizedDescription)","    }","","    image = snapshot?.image","}"]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Related-examples","text":"Related examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Create a static map snapshot, learn how to use the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter"},{"text":" to generate a static image based on an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object’s style, camera, and view bounds.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStylable"